  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg4149">msg4149 (view)</a></th>
   <th>Author: brittag</th>
   <th>Date: 2014-02-28.22:09:41</th>
   <th>
    
   </th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>To help encourage visitors to stay engaged with OpenHatch, let's add a widget to the homepage to 
prompt them to sign up for useful mailing lists. (The blog has this already in its sidebar - 
<a href="http://openhatch.org/blog/">http://openhatch.org/blog/</a> )

This could be a little paragraph in the "Join our community" box, with text like this:

"Keep in touch with us! Subscribe to our announcements lists (newsletters and events) to hear 
occasional updates about what we're working on:"

Where "newsletters" would link to <a href="http://lists.openhatch.org/pipermail/announce/">http://lists.openhatch.org/pipermail/announce/</a> - and "events" 
would link to the new events-announce list described at <a href="http://lists.openhatch.org/pipermail/devel/2014-February/003468.html">http://lists.openhatch.org/pipermail/devel/2014-February/003468.html</a>

And there would be a "subscribe" box that ideally subscribes you to both email lists.

I've attached a tiny mockup!</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
